<h2>About Me</h2>
<div class='widget-content'>
<a href='https://plus.google.com/113072710534870591381'><img alt='My Photo' class='profile-img' height='80' src='//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-jbKYOfdiGGI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB4E/Ng9brfwxz0w/s512-c/photo.jpg' width='80'/></a>
<dl class='profile-datablock'>
<dt class='profile-data'>
<a class='profile-name-link g-profile' href='https://plus.google.com/113072710534870591381' rel='author' style='background-image: url(//www.google.com/images/icons/ui/gprofile_button-16.png);'>
Brett Scott
</a>
<br/>
<div class='g-follow' data-annotation='bubble' data-height='20' data-href='https://plus.google.com/113072710534870591381'></div>
</dt>
<dd class='profile-textblock'>I explore economic systems.&#160;I have a book called&#160;<i><a href="http://www.plutobooks.com/display.asp?K=9780745333502&amp;" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">The Heretic&#39;s Guide to Global Finance: Hacking the Future of Money</a></i>, published with Pluto Press.&#160;I&#39;ve written for publications like the <i>Guardian</i>, <i>Wired, New Scientist,</i>&#160;<i>Ecologist</i>, <i>New Internationalist</i>, <i>Aeon Mag&#160;</i>&amp; <i>openDemocracy</i> and have appeared on shows such as BBC <i>World Update</i>, BBC <i>Newsday</i>, the <i>Keiser Report</i>, and Arte TV<i>.</i>&#160;I&#39;ve worked as a broker, barman and blues musician, and I&#39;m a Fellow at the&#160;<a href="http://thefinancelab.org/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Finance Innovation Lab</a>.&#160;I blog <a href="http://www.suitpossum.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">here</a>&#160;and&#160;tweet as&#160;<a href="https://twitter.com/#!/Suitpossum" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">@Suitpossum</a>.</dd>
</dl>
